  "prompt": "What is cognition?",
  "response": "Cognition refers to the mental processes involved in acquiring knowledge and understanding. These processes include thinking, knowing, remembering, judging, and problem-solving. Cognition encompasses a wide range of functions such as perception, attention, memory, language, and executive functions (like planning and decision making). It enables individuals to process information, apply knowledge in various contexts, develop concepts, and navigate the world effectively. Essentially, cognition is fundamental to how we interpret and interact with our environment.",
